      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The claims are largely rooted in historical assertions and interpretations of sovereignty, often overlapping in the contested waters. China's expansive \"nine-dash line\" claim is widely disputed by international legal bodies, particularly the 2016 Permanent Court of Arbitration ruling against it. While some nations adhere to UNCLOS (United Nations Convention on the Law of the Sea), the actions of claimant states often prioritize national interests over strict international legal compliance. This legal ambiguity is what keeps the situation highly volatile.",
